                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 6.202,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The opinions of the Court in two cases will be announced by Justice Thomas."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 6.202,
                        "stop": 267.075,
                        "byte_start": 0,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15100,
                            "name": "Clarence Thomas",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/clarence_thomas",
                            "last_name": "Thomas",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2744,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 688194000,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "George H. W. Bush",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2744"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32680,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 49064,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/clarence_thomas.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 8870,
                            "identifier": "clarence_thomas"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 6.202,
                                "stop": 13.207,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "First case I have to announce is Hunt versus Cromartie, number 98-85."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 13.207,
                                "stop": 19.269,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "This case comes to us on appeal from the United States District Court for the Eastern District of North Carolina."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 19.269,
                                "stop": 28.474,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "In Shaw versus Hunt, we held that the North Carolina\u2019s District 12, was a product of an unconstitutional racial gerrymander."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 28.474,
                                "stop": 34.389,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "In response to our decision, the State enacted a new districting plan."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 34.389,
                                "stop": 49.017,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Appellees, however believed that the (Inaudible) also was unconstitutionally informed and brought suit against several state officials seeking to enjoin elections from being held pursuant to this new plan."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 49.017,
                                "stop": 57.87,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Before discovery and without an evidentiary hearing, the District Court granted summary judgment in appellee\u0027s favor and entered in an injunction."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 57.87,
                                "stop": 67.487,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "In the District Court\u2019s view, the uncontroverted material facts showed that the State used racial criteria in drawing District 12."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 67.487,
                                "stop": 71.095,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "In our opinion filed with the Clerk today, we reverse."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 71.095,
                                "stop": 76.057,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Districting legislation ordinarily, is race neutral on its face."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 76.057,
                                "stop": 81.031,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "It classifies tracts of land, precincts or census blocks."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 81.031,
                                "stop": 86.405,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The task of assessing a jurisdiction\u2019s motive therefore is an inherently complex endeavor."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 86.405,
                                "stop": 93.02,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "One requiring careful inquiry into such circumstantial and direct evidence as may be available."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 93.02,
                                "stop": 99.13,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Appellees presented evidence showing District 12, size, shape and alleged lack of continuity."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 99.13,
                                "stop": 118.293,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "They also presented statistical and demographic evidence reporting to show that at several points along District 12\u2019s boundary, heavily black districts were included within District 12, while precincts that were equally democratic in terms of voter registration were excluded."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 118.293,
                                "stop": 129.262,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "On the whole and viewed in light of our prior cases appellee\u0027s evidence tends to support an inference that the State drew its district lines with an impressible racial motivation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 129.262,
                                "stop": 134.729,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "But summary judgment is appropriate only where there is no genuine issue of material fact."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 134.729,
                                "stop": 140.746,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The State\u2019s motivation is a factual question and was sufficiently put in dispute by appellants."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 140.746,
                                "stop": 147.949,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Appellants argue that the State\u2019s districting plan was drawn with the intent to make District 12, a strong democratic district."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 147.949,
                                "stop": 152.194,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "They supported their contention with affidavits from two state legislatives."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 152.194,
                                "stop": 166.625,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "More important they offered affidavit testimony from an expert witness, who analyze voting results in addition to party registration figures and who examined District 12\u2019s entire border as oppose to select points along that border."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 166.625,
                                "stop": 176.92,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "In the expert\u2019s view the underlying data supported a political motivation at least as well as and somewhat better than a racial explanation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 176.92,
                                "stop": 192.499,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Accepting appellants political motivation explanation as true as is required at the summary judgment stage, the fact of the legislature\u2019s motivation was in dispute and appellees were not entitled to judgment as matter of law."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 192.499,
                                "stop": 210.145,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "A jurisdiction may engage in constitutional political gerrymandering, even if it so happens that the most loyal democrats are black democrats, and even if the State\u2019s legislature was conscious of that fact."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 210.145,
                                "stop": 222.604,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We do not hold that summary judgment may be never be held in the plaintiff\u2019s favor in a racial gerrymandering case like this one, sought to be proved exclusively by circumstantial evidence."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 222.604,
                                "stop": 233.936,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We can\u2019t imagine an instance where the reasonable inference is to be drawn in the non moving party\u2019s favor would not be significantly probative so as to create a genuine issue of material fact."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 233.936,
                                "stop": 237.459,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "But appellant\u2019s evidence is not of that character."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 237.459,
                                "stop": 240.476,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We also do not express position on the merits."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 240.476,
                                "stop": 249.786,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The District Court is more familiar with the evidence than we are, and it may turn out, that the appellees prove their claim to the state acted with an impermissible motivation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 249.786,
                                "stop": 258.266,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Summary judgment however is inappropriate when the evidence is susceptible of different interpretations or inferences by the prior fact."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 258.266,
                                "stop": 267.075,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Stevens has filed an opinion concurring in the judgment which Justices Souter, Ginsberg and Breyer have joined."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
